frameDefinitions: A Resource is depleted by some process, resulting in there being only a Remainder in existence some time into or after the process.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
This scenario describes a series of Events, associated with a single Participant, i.e., the history of the Participant.
An Employee has a Position doing work in a particular Field, or doing work on a particular Task, for which an Employer gives Compensation to the Employee.

An Experiencer actualizes a certain pattern of behavior, a Lifestyle, which persists for a significant period of time in the Experiencer's life and is recognized as part of his character or normal routine.
An Agent expends effort towards achieving a Goal.
frameExamples: There are only two poems <t>left</t> from Quayle
We've been worried about our recent hire's <t><fex name='Events'>history</fex></t> of deceiving employers.
Undocumented foreigners are <t>working</t> as  building contractors for Laing Builders.
He <t>lived</t> a hedonistic life before he settled down.
In addition, our organization will <t>work</t> on improving accountability in every department.
listRoleDefinitions: The part of the Resource that the Process has not yet applied to.
The original set of items to which the Depletive_process applies one after the other.
The individual who owned the Resource that is being depleted.

A temporal setting or event which metonymically stands for the entities that were in existence then. The <fen>Remainder</fen> is part of the <fen>Original_context</fen>. This role occurs especially when abstract entities such as social institutions are seen as <fen>Resource</fen>s.
The Time when the amount of the Resource that is let is assessed.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.

The <fen>Participant</fen> is either an active participant in all of the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Agent or Patient), or is more peripherally associated with the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Location or Topic).
The <fen>Events</fen> which the <fen>Participant</fen> is a part of. This role is used to mark the frame-evoking element.
When the <fen>Events</fen> concerning the <fen>Participant</fen> occured.
The <fen>Employee</fen> is obligated to perform a <fen>Task</fen> in order to receive <fen>Compensation</fen>.
The <fen>Employer</fen> gives <fen>Compensation</fen> to an <fen>Employee</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place_of_employment</fen> of the <fen>Employee</fen>.
The label given to a particular type of employment.
The <fen>Employee</fen> is obligated to perform the <fen>Task</fen> to recieve <fen>Compensation</fen> from the <fen>Employer</fen> .
This role identifies the <fen>Field</fen> in which one works.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> period during which an <fen>Employee</fen>  works for an <fen>Employer</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Employee</fen> works.
The person who actualizes a pattern of behavior.
A pattern of behavior which the actions of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> matches for a significant period of time.
The <fen>Lifestyle</fen> may be characterized by a <fen>Manner</fen>, which is often expressed adverbially.
A temporal description of when the <fen>Experiencer</fen> adopts a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
The spatial location where the <fen>Experiencer</fen> carries out a <fen>Lifestyle</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> puts effort into reaching <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> expends effort to achieve.
An entity that is centrally involved in the <fen>Goal</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to acheive.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the effort occurs.
The place where the work is done.
